Please squash these into a single review.  Moving these applications one at a time makes it hard to review the overall structure.
I don't quite get this - why (and which) files are smaller? Is it the meson.build?
I support this overall, My only comment can best be characterized as a nit.
This looks a little odd.  Should we have a dependency declared that this can just inherit instead of the ".." ?
does test_IpmbSensor.cpp need to move as well to keep the folder structure the same? (and this test() stanza move into test/src?

I don't think sentence really conveys what you've done here.

Also, a process is an instance of an application. I think it would be better to use the 'application' here and throughout the commit message as the repository does not deal with processes.

How about:

> Move source files into application-specific sub-directories

This isn't yet done, as your commit message in PS7 still talks about processes :)

> use the 'application' here and throughout the commit message

I think splitting the source into application-specific subdirectories is a good move, however, can you please match the directory names to the associated meson options (including making them all lower-case).
